Let's go, Rusty.

157
00:21:29,533 --> 00:21:32,331
We've checked everything, sir.
The storeroom's gone.

158
00:21:32,536 --> 00:21:36,597
No torpedoes, no motors,
no spare parts, no nothing.

159
00:21:43,447 --> 00:21:46,211
Wonder if they have
any torpedoes at Corregidor.

160
00:21:47,017 --> 00:21:49,747
-Might be.
-l'll check on it.

161
00:21:59,530 --> 00:22:00,861
Hi.

162
00:22:02,299 --> 00:22:03,357
A little rugged.

163
00:22:07,271 --> 00:22:10,900
You got wet clothes on
underneath that blanket?

164
00:22:11,108 --> 00:22:12,939
Just scared.

165
00:22:14,411 --> 00:22:16,572
You haven't got
a monopoly on that.

166
00:22:23,420 --> 00:22:24,717
What are you looking at?

167
00:22:24,922 --> 00:22:28,119
Just looking for the Arizona
to come steaming up to base...

168
00:22:28,325 --> 00:22:30,657
...with her 1 4-inch guns blazing...

169
00:22:30,861 --> 00:22:33,421
...and the best cook stoves
in the Navy.

170
00:22:34,565 --> 00:22:36,123
Arizona ?

171
00:22:43,641 --> 00:22:45,131
Arizona.

172
00:22:55,552 --> 00:22:59,113
Some Army boys told us a Jap task force
is headed for Lingayen Gulf.

173
00:22:59,323 --> 00:23:02,019
-Planes spotted it at sunset.
-Must be another landing.

174
00:23:02,226 --> 00:23:03,921
Lingayen?

175
00:23:06,230 --> 00:23:07,857
Give me those scissors, Doc.

176
00:23:08,065 --> 00:23:11,034
That's only about
200 miles from here.

177
00:23:12,436 --> 00:23:13,801
Two thirty-five.

178
00:23:14,004 --> 00:23:15,767
Why don't we knock those babies off?

179
00:23:15,973 --> 00:23:19,409
What with? A cake of soap
and a bathtub? Give me that pencil.

180
00:23:29,586 --> 00:23:32,714
Mr. Brickley, the admiral, sir.
Right away.

181
00:23:33,424 --> 00:23:35,449
Check your gasoline.

182
00:23:36,193 --> 00:23:37,490
Feel better?

183
