-Yes?
-Brickley.

187
00:23:57,848 --> 00:23:59,713
Mr. Brickley, sir.

188
00:24:02,219 --> 00:24:03,186
You sent for me?

189
00:24:03,387 --> 00:24:07,153
Yes, get a boat ready
to move my staff to Corregidor.

190
00:24:08,726 --> 00:24:11,593
You'll run messenger trips
between Manila and The Rock.

191
00:24:12,429 --> 00:24:15,262
Work out a schedule
with the Chief of Staff.

192
00:24:18,635 --> 00:24:21,433
Cavite is finished as a base.

193
00:24:21,805 --> 00:24:24,968
Move your outfit
to Sisiman Cove on Bataan.

194
00:24:28,145 --> 00:24:29,976
ls that all, sir?

195
00:24:30,180 --> 00:24:31,772
That's all.

196
00:24:35,552 --> 00:24:40,148
ls it true that a Jap task force
is moving into Lingayen Gulf, sir?

197
00:24:42,226 --> 00:24:43,887
Type that and send it.

198
00:24:47,297 --> 00:24:48,889
Sit down, Brickley.

199
00:24:55,506 --> 00:24:57,906
That task force will land.

200
00:24:58,108 --> 00:25:00,076
You and l can't stop it.

201
00:25:00,878 --> 00:25:05,042
Pearl Harbor was a disaster,
like the Spanish Armada.

202
00:25:06,350 --> 00:25:07,374
Listen, son...

203
00:25:08,619 --> 00:25:10,883
...you and l are professionals.

204
00:25:11,088 --> 00:25:15,616
lf the manager says, ''Sacrifice,''
we lay down a bunt...

205
00:25:15,826 --> 00:25:18,818
...and let somebody else
hit the home runs.

206
00:25:19,396 --> 00:25:21,193
We know about those destroyers...

207
00:25:21,398 --> 00:25:24,265
...out of commission,
tied up around San Diego.

208
00:25:24,902 --> 00:25:26,836
We could use them here...

209
00:25:27,271 --> 00:25:28,670
...but they're not around.

210
00:25:29,406 --> 00:25:30,873
They won't be.

211
00:25:31,875 --> 00:25:35,242
Our job is to lay down
that sacrifice.

212
00:25:36,046 --> 00:25:38,571
That's what we were trained for.

213
00:25:38,782 --> 00:25:40,409
That's what we'll do.

214
00:25:41,752 --> 00:25:43,242
Understand?

215
00:25:58,135 --> 00:25:59,568
Thank you.

216
00:26:03,140 --> 00:26:04,630
All set, sir.

217
00:26:07,377 --> 00:26:08,901
Secure your boats.

218
00:26:09,113 --> 00:26:10,842
Secure the boats?

219
00:26:11,048 --> 00:26:14,279
Shorty, take the admiral
and his staff to Corregidor.

220
00:26:15,119 --> 00:26:19,419
Lefty, you stand by to run
a messenger trip daily at 900.

221
00:26:19,723 --> 00:26:22,851
The rest of you
take your boats to Sisiman Cove.

222
00:26:23,527 --> 00:26:25,324
You join us there.

223
00:26:37,407 --> 00:26:39,637
Are you kidding, Brick?

224
00:26:40,210 --> 00:26:42,701
Theirs not to reason why,
theirs but to do--

225
00:26:42,913 --> 00:26:44,107
And die.

226
00:26:44,314 --> 00:26:47,442
l don't want to be bored
to death running messages.

227
00:26:48,051 --> 00:26:51,350
l'll see that you get
the more intriguing ones.

228
00:26:54,158 --> 00:26:55,716
Does that help?

229
00:28:24,948 --> 00:28:26,040
Any chow, Brick?

230
00:28:26,617 --> 00:28:29,745
-Razor blades and toothpaste.
-That's a swell diet.

231
00:28:29,953 --> 00:28:33,719
